We adopt systematic literature review approach (SLR) based on PRISMA to identify, screen and filter appropriate, peer-reviewed and grey literature from various scientific databases (Fig. 3
                     ): English databases (Google Scholar, Science Direct, Web of Science, Scopus) and Chinese databases (CNKI and Wan-Fang), which are comprehensive and cover a wide range of areas in various disciplines. The following keywords and phrases are used: ‘ageing’, ‘elderly people’, ‘older people’, ‘older adult’, ‘older ages', ‘elderly care centre/buildings', ‘aged care homes/buildings', ‘nursing home’, ‘physical health’, ‘green infrastructure’, ‘vegetation’, ‘indoor gardens', ‘indoor plants', ‘green walls', ‘green space’, ‘green roofs', ‘green balconies/terraces', 'trees', ‘lawns,’, ‘hedges and shrubs', ‘garden’, ‘park’, ‘air quality’, ‘air pollution’, ‘traffic pollution’, ‘thermal environment’, ‘thermal stress', ‘thermal comfort’, ‘urban heat island’, ‘microclimate’, ‘monitoring’, ‘modelling’, ‘simulation’, ‘building environment design’, ‘indoor design’, ‘landscape design’, ‘spatial layout’, 'species', 'aesthetics', 'access' and ‘fire prevention’. Our search is limited to publications in English and Chinese in the last 20 years. This search has resulted in 10,015 articles; of which 9006 articles are eliminated because of their low relevance. The remaining 1009 articles are then further screened for content and study focus. Other relevant articles may have been excluded because of the language and search of the database. Finally, 219 appropriate articles are discussed in detail. Fig. 4
                      shows that only 7.74% and 4.87% of the studies are relevant to design and ECCs, respectively. Most of the works are from Europe (47.95%) and Asia (28.31%).
